Code of Conduct
Introduction
We are committed to creating a welcoming and inclusive environment for all participants. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for behavior and the consequences for unacceptable behavior.

Our Standards
Be Respectful: Treat everyone with respect. Listen to others and consider their perspectives.
Be Inclusive: We welcome people from all backgrounds. Everyone should feel safe and valued.
Be Responsible: Take responsibility for your actions and their impact on others.
Be Supportive: Encourage others and offer help when needed.
Unacceptable Behavior
Examples of unacceptable behavior include, but are not limited to:

Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination.
Disruptive or disrespectful behavior.
Inappropriate language or imagery.
Reporting
If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it to the designated contact (provide contact details here).

Enforcement
Consequences for violating this Code of Conduct may include:

A warning.
Temporary or permanent ban from the community.
Acknowledgment
By participating in this community, you agree to abide by this Code of Conduct.
